# Performance Guidelines

## Keep Changes Incremental

- Make small, focused changes — one thing at a time
- Avoid large-scale refactoring in a single step
- Break complex tasks into phases
- Verify after each phase before continuing

## Complexity Management

Avoid last 20% of context window for:
- Large-scale refactoring spanning multiple files
- Feature implementation across many modules
- Debugging complex multi-file interactions

Prefer for constrained context:
- Single-file edits
- Independent utility creation
- Documentation updates
- Simple bug fixes

## For Complex Tasks

When facing a complex multi-step task:
1. Plan the approach before writing any code
2. Break it into independent subtasks
3. Complete and verify each subtask before moving on
4. Use a structured critique pass before finalizing

## Build Troubleshooting

If build fails:
1. Read the full error message before acting
2. Fix one error at a time, starting from the top
3. Re-run after each fix to check for cascading issues
4. Verify the fix didn't introduce new failures
